" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104wyl1665702688770.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/wyl1665702688770.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/wyl1665702688770.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"wyl1665702688770\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Library </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Specifies the library containing the global objects used by the component or\n      application shell. If no library is specified, the library defined for the application shell\n      is used. Otherwise, SYSTEM_LIBRARY is used as the default. </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"wyl1665702688770__section_w1103ab1b5b1_w1104ab1b5_w1105ab1\">\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"wyl1665702688770__table_d10916e1_d10917e1_d10918e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Expected Value: </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> String of up to 32 characters. Supports\n                        Unicode. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Default Value: </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> None </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"wyl1665702688770__section_bx5_51k_4wb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d458200e85\">Applies To</h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"wyl1665702688770__ul_jnw_v1k_4wb\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wyl1665702688770__li_d39560e1_d39561e1_d39562e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"dhu1704688959391.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/dhu1704688959391.html\" title=\"Uniface application components are interchangeable software modules that handle application processing. They are technology-independent, so compiled components can be run on any operating system.\">Components</a></li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wyl1665702688770__li_d39563e1_d39564e1_d39565e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"yye1705472567076.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/yye1705472567076.html\" title=\"An application shell is the first object that is executed when a Windows or character mode application is started. It determines how the application is initialized and the first form component that is displayed.\">Application Shells for Desktop Applications</a></li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wyl1665702688770__li_d39566e1_d39567e1_d39568e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"lfh1665702880070.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lfh1665702880070.html\" title=\"A server shell defines the behavior of an application server, which is responsible for executing remote components such as server pages and services.\">Application Shells for Servers</a></li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kee1692183917031.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Libraries</a><p>Libraries are collections of objects that can be shared in some way, either during development, or at runtime. They are main development objects, so whenever they are saved or exported, all the objects that they contain are included.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3616848\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3616848\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Library Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 09, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Library Specifies the library containing the global objects used by the component or application shell. If no library is specified, the library defined for the application shell is used. Otherwise, SYSTEM_LIBRARY is used as the default. Expected Value: String of up to 32 characters. Supports Unicode. Default Value: None Applies To Components Application Shells for Desktop Applications Application Shells for Servers Related Links Libraries Libraries are collections of objects that can be shared in some way, either during development, or at runtime. They are main development objects, so whenever 